<br>
1)  Guild Hellos and Welcomes to our new and returning members.<br>
<br>
2)  A discussion of recruiting:<br>
    a.  the good progress in recruiting based on the new <br>
        guidelines and player support.<br>
    b.  use of the Forum and guideline recruiting post for<br>
        all potential recruits (have them go to site).<br>
    c.  tremendous support out of guild members and<br>
        adherence to posted guidelines.<br>
    d.  Designated Recruitment Officers (RO) and discussed<br>
        i)  Duties of RO include: recruit evaluation, <br>
            recommendation monitoring, forum monitoring, <br>
            recruit grouping, recruit discussions and <br>
            information, guild invites, and all point-of<br>
            contact administration business of recruiting.<br>
       ii)  RO is to be a rotational position held by two<br>
            officers for the month (Treasurer exempt from <br>
            this duty).<br>
      iii)  ROs duty to know all recruitment info and be <br>
            aware of their rotation; members duty to know<br>
            who the ROs for the month are and use them as<br>
            point-of-contact for all recruitment issues.<br>
    e.  Mordwin and Teynor designated for this month's duty<br>
        as Recruitment Officer (RO).<br>
    f.  Members are encouraged to only contact these ROs<br>
        for recruitment quesions etc, OR contact the nearest<br>
        Officer if no RO is online.<br>
<br>
3)  Twinking rules were briefly covered to illustrate that 'twinking' has been relaxed BUT not eliminated as a guild rule.  Use your heads and hearts people, you know when you are uber twinked, etc.<br>
<br>
4)  Guild Involvement by ALL members was discussed to include the following points:<br>
    a.  grouping/group planning - Guild is encouraged to<br>
        PLAN groups rather than wait for someone else to do<br>
        it for them.  A group rarely will just come looking<br>
        you.  You are all familiar with the game enough to <br>
        plan and execute your own groups.  This is <br>
        encouraged from the highest level to the lowest.<br>
        If you cant find a group, part of the problem is<br>
        that your not doing enough planning for one.  Get<br>
        involved; plan it and do it.  This has been<br>
        occurring much more frequently and is EXTREMELY<br>
        beneficial to the guild and all members.<br>
    b.  raid/event planning - SEE a. above.  This is very<br>
        similar to group planning.  Dont wait for something<br>
        to come your way.  Plan it, announce it, and do it.<br>
        Not every raid or event has to be planned by the<br>
        Officer Corps.  Plan raids/farms/events within your<br>
        level and means.  This has been occurring lately to,<br>
        somewhat.  Get involved and get to it ).<br>
    c.  GAME TIME:  Please appreciate others' time in the<br>
        game.  Remember, we all pay to play, and we are all<br>
        one big family.  So respect others' playing time <br>
        always.  No one in this guild is at another's beck<br>
        and call.  We are all a family here simply because <br>
        we choose to be.<br>
<br>
5)  The Guild Treasury was discussed.  Please see the Treasury Section within the main Guild Forum for a list of rules for this support mechanism.  The following topics were hit too:<br>
    a.  The Treasury is a tool of support aimed at Guild <br>
        strength.  Its aim is a repository for items that<br>
        may be rotated within the guild and among its<br>
        members for the purpose of member strength, and<br>
        thus overall guild strength.<br>
    b.  The Treasurer is the arbiter of rotation of items <br>
        within the Treasury, under guidance of the Officer<br>
        Corps.<br>
    c.  ONLY CONTACT THE TREASURER THROUGH THE FORUM.  He<br>
        has been instructed to ignore all tells in game <br>
        concerning the rotation of items in either category<br>
        (IN or OUT).  REMEMBER: he has a game to play too.<br>
    d.  Abuse of the Treasury will not be tolerated by any<br>
        member for any reason.  The Treasury is a support <br>
        instrument for all, and not the personal pawn shop<br>
        of any member.  The Treasurer, and Officer Corps,<br>
        will consistently monitor the use of the Treasury <br>
        by all members to ensure fairness for the Guild.<br>
        Remember, if you abuse the Treasury you run the risk<br>
        of ensuring no one puts items in it anymore.  In<br>
        this event, everyone would lose, especially the <br>
        Guild as a whole.  Be fair and honorable.<br>
<br>
6)  Promotions were discussed, as was the process the Officer Corps selects those to be promoted.  The process involves a full Officer Corps vote on the NEED of new officers, and all members to be reviewed for promotion.  No single officer has a louder voice in this process to ensure fairness.  The Officer Corps recently identified the need to promote 3 members in status.  This was reached by unanimous decision and vote.  Additionally, the Officer Corps selected 3 members to receive promotion after reviewing ALL members within the guild.  Members promoted to Officer include:  Ilrissa, Taansey, and Gajiin.  Please congratulate them when you see them online as they have worked very long and hard to receive these promotions.  Remember, accepting a promotion ensures a full regimen of work and responsibility while in the game.  Duties include RO, Raid/Event Planner, etc.  These officers have agreed to work for the entire guild tirelessly, and we should honor them accordingly.  Congratulations to all of you!<br>
<br>
Mordwin Kordravvia<br>
47th circle of Flamecaller<br>
Porter to the Planes<br>
Guild Leader of The Sentinent Family<br>
